race.description: Barron Mechanical & Big Sky Experience Mdn Plate
race.comment: SUPREME STYLE (10) resumes after finishing in the minor money at all three runs in her career thus far. Winkers go on for the first time and looks primed to get off the mark from the low draw. Clearly the one to beat. GOOD TIME (1) had trialled very well at Wellington in readiness for his debut but ended up a long way back after being slowly away. He never really got into the race from that point on and finished 5.7L away after jumping a $3.40 chance. He was also slow to recover on a day where nothing went right. Happy to forgive that effort off what he showed at the trials and he can bounce back in a big way. NANDOWRIE (3) showed enough in his recent trial at Forbes to suggest he can run a good race here on debut. Not to be discounted. STREET SKATER (4) can make his presence felt off a freshen.
